summary_title: psalter

value: made for a Duchess of Breslau between 1255 and 1267; Bertram, fourth earl of Ashburnham (1797 – 1878), Ashburnham Appendix, no. XXXIV; purchased from him by Henry Yates Thompson (1838 – 1928) in May 1897 (his bookplate inside upper cover); his sale, Sotheby’s, London, 23 March 1920, lot 60; purchased by Thomas H. Riches (1856 – 1935); his bequest, 1935 (received in 1950).
